-- Turkish Jets Strike PKK Camps in Northern Iraq, Armed Forces Say
-- B y   E m r e   P e k e r
-- 2012-02-04T12:27:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/turkish-jets-strike-pkk-camps-in-northern-iraq-armed-forces-say.html
Turkish jets struck Kurdistan
Workers’ Party, or PKK, camps in northern  Iraq , the military
General Staff said.  Turkey ’s air force attacked three targets yesterday,
according to a  statement  published on the Ankara-based
organization’s website.  The PKK, which is listed as a terrorist organization by
Turkey, the U.S. and the European Union, has been fighting for
autonomy in southeastern Turkey for three decades and has its
command center in Iraq’s Kandil Mountains.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emre Peker in Ankara at 
 epeker2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  